replies.bodyText:
I had proposed reusing the reflect cache to avoid growing the default footprint of j.l.Class but as pointed out, the CHM is a lot of overhead here.  Looking at the j.l.Class, there are a number of existing caches:
* private transient AnnotationCache annotationCache;
* private transient AnnotationVars annotationVars;
* private transient ClassRepositoryHolder classRepoHolder;
* private transient ReflectCache reflectCache;
* private transient Class<?> cachedDeclaringClass;
* private transient Class<?> cachedEnclosingClass;  // getting enclosingClass also caches declaringClass
* private transient Class<?>[] cachedInterfaces;
* private transient Object methodHandleCache;

An alternative would be to add a new cache that holds the {cachedDeclaringClass, cachedEnclosingClass, cachedInterfaces} & the new two SoftReferences for cached names.
This would require more performance and footprint results to validate it doesn't regress startup / throughput / footprint.
Thoughts?

